</noscript></center><div class='main'><div class='mainheader'><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="178dc98989d669ff4092283ae3e60f13" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></div><div class='maincontent'><font class="h1font"> Flashback: Come Fly (Sail) Away, Repeat X 2 WITH MEEEE!!!!!!<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><font class="afont"> Not Reviewed</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/heroclix/main/mpage.php?member=17490'>Jason "magerunner" McLaughlin</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/heroclix/main/mpage.php?member=17490&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 24, 2005</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> [This artical was originaly submitted Sonof Vader under the name below.  I feel that most of the ideas are still solid and merit a look at in today TK heavy game.  All credit goes to Andrew and his wander rant of an artical very well explains his side.  I have listed his home page for reference, there are plenty of team ideas and articals.  <br />
<br />
Until next time, look back to go forward.]<br />
<br />
Come Fly (Sail) Away, Repeat X 2 WITH MEEEE!!!!!!<br />
Andrew &quot;SonofVader&quot; Chamberlain <http://www.decktech.net/heroclix/main/mpage.php?member=15684><br />
<br />
Basic stipulation: SonofVader is long-winded. Hence, his articles are as well. Please, don&#39;t try to read this in one sitting unless you&#39;ve got some time on your hands. <br />
<br />
Once, long ago, WizKids did something really stupid and allowed for this magical ability called &quot;Taxiing&quot;. While seemingly great, it wasn&#39;t playtested thoroughly enough and created a sharp unbalance in the game. The result? HeroClix 2.0 (known by some as Indy Clix Rules, by others as a stupid waste of a game) created to new stipulations for fliers that severely limited their abilities: NAAT (No Action After Taxi - a term coined by my friend hair10) and FCCF (Fliers Can&#39;t Carry Fliers - a dumb acronym that has no pronunciation value). The result? Many fliers were dumped into &quot;meat boxes&quot; (a term for extra figures or containers with extra pork) or were lit on fire and launched into the air with yells following them, such as &quot;Let&#39;s see you fly now, jackass&quot; or &quot;Firelord isn&#39;t broken, he&#39;s melted!!&quot; or my personal favorite, &quot;Why the hell did I just light my figure on fire and throw it in the air? Oh well, I guess I&#39;ll have another St. Pauli&#39;s Girl.&quot; However, the flaming pieces of plastic are necessary, useful, and most importantly, just as effective as they were before. <br />
<br />
First things first, go read the article entitled The Cavalry, it gives you an idea of how to work some fliers (though it only scratches the surface of what these beasts can now do). <br />
<br />
Now, onto the real show. Time to get crackin&#39;. <br />
<br />
With the onslaught of new figures with Critical Mass, one thing notably missing from a Marvel/ DC set is a ton of REV fliers. This one has 4 (though 10/ 12 uniques have it). Angel (I refuse to call RV anything but Angel), Brood Warrior and Queen and Moonstone/ Meteorite are all fliers. Indy only gave us two fliers, and they were both uniques. So, in the past two sets, we&#39;re being taught how to live without taxis. However, THIS DOESN&#39;T MAKE THEM ANY LESS EFFECTIVE! Under the new rules, you can still taxi figures. A TKing taxi is even better (Fatality, Cos Boy, Sersi, Moondragon, and so on and so forth). Keeping this in mind, we can see how a dual figure might be better. You can carry a figure one turn, TK them even further the next, TK a figure one turn, taxi up a second one the next, etc. This strategy works best if the fare (figure carried by taxi) has a free ability and can follow up with an attack of their own the next turn (something similar to Stealth, Outwit, Perplex, Enhancement, Defend, Hydra/ Defenders/ JSA/ Sinister Syndicate/ team abilities along those lines... basically, anything that does not require an action to kick into gear). This means that your taxi (a front gunner) is now vital to the core of your fighting squad: think of them, instead of taxis, as very awkward guns, and the fares are now bayonets... nope, don&#39;t do that. It&#39;s a terrible analogy. Instead, think of them as taxis that either have chainsaws on them (close combat taxis) or rocket launchers (ranged combat). Those would be awesome taxis. Then, we could have dancers dancing in the streets, cheering on these vehicles of death. And I would be king. <br />
<br />
Since I&#39;m not king, we have more to look at: specifically, how fliers work now. Do you have a stealthed figure that needs a taxi? You do? Then why not fly them around with a free mover. Hawkman gets charge, and Carter Hall has leadership. Combine that with Nightwing, and you&#39;ve got a nasty 1-2 combo that can take down any 6-9 click figure (provided you push with Carter the next turn). Free movers with stealth fare are still solid. Wasp is very effective at getting around Black Panther, and if you move it to U Wasp and E Black Panther, you have dual Inc and BCF to go along with that Outwit, a formidable combo. I&#39;ve seen too many teams sacrificing fliers to just get damage figures into the fray. With so much stealth, a taxi that can carry the fare around the back way and they close in on medics and TKers really turns the tables on your opponent. Using Firelord as an 11 or 12 move taxi one turn, then blasting away the next is still one of my favorite moves (much less cheesy, still very effective). Having Firelord carry around Black Panther or Psylocke works even better. Having GL carry around Batman, Nightwing and Deathstroke is just sick (keep this one for 400 point games). Please, don’t do this against friends. It’s not as bad as messing around with their mother, but it’s still very high on the list of things “not to do.” <br />
<br />
Another point for these silly people with clear plastic bases is that of flying. A cheap flier is a quick and easy way to get over to your opponent (provided they aren&#39;t playing around indoors). Simply start Hawkman or Vulture or whomever you&#39;re using for Charge/ Running Shot in soaring. Then, lazily move them to the backfield with them, keeping them out of everyone’s range, and bam, hit up the backfield figures for a nasty blow to support. Many excellent support killers were used as taxis back in the day… now they’re different figures… Booster Gold was once the nastiest taxi in the game. Now, with his high move and 8 range, you can run him to the back field and take care of medics and other what not. Using him in tandem with Hawkman keeps an old 1-2 combo alive, and they both can really take out the backfield. Then, move them up front for a nasty flanking maneuver. <br />
<br />
Fliers also do not have to stop if they come into base contact with an opponent’s figure. First off, that means if there’s a clear line to the backfield, you can just cut through your opponent’s forces and not have to worry about stopping (just don’t end at a point where your opponent can base your Archangel bent on murdering his Paramedic). Also, flying Super Strength figures can yoink objects out from under stealthed characters, opening up people to a whole new world of pain. Fury can now commence with the stealing of objects, fun for all. <br />
<br />
When it’s all said and done, fliers have created a whole new fluid way of playing. Teams that were focused on taxi shoot must now looking to other viable ways of taking down figures. Taxi a beatstick in. Next turn, scoot over to the medic and take them out. It gets nasty. Green Goblin gets really nasty. Ick. <br />
<br />
So, understanding fliers, how they work and some different strategies for them, how can you compete against a flier? Simple: with more fliers. The severe undercosted ability to stay out of range for almost any opponent that isn’t soaring creates an unbalance. By rebalancing this with other fliers, it will actually create two levels of attack from which games will be competed on. Other ways to take care of fliers: long range figures, Leap/ Climb, anyone with RCE (can always be used against fliers unless you’re based by a non-flier as well). Any of these tactics are strikingly painful to overcome when played right (but then again, just moving figures into soaring does wonders for escape). Further, by allowing for more fluid gameplay, it’s much harder to pin down an opponent’s strategy. The fliers may still be fully operating on a hovering level against one opponent who doesn’t think in terms of this new 3 dimensional battlefield, while the next one may play a team of Running Shot/ Charging Soarers, hell bent on never allowing you to get a shot in. These new gameplay tactics call for a more intricate style of viewing how individual games are actually played. Pay attention to the little flight stick on your figures and your opponent’s. It actually means something now. <br />
<br />
So, with all of this in the bag, who are the best figures to use with the new flying strategies? Instead of listing every flier in the game, I’m going to try out a few that I like or that may have great potential. You can do the same if you want, and leave strategies for individual figures on reviews… it’ll help out everyone. First off, soaring Chargers are a blast. Vulture, Hawkman, Archangel, Wonder Woman… all excellent. I actually put them in soaring more than anyone else. Also, Running Shot figures are excellent (and by keeping them soaring, it’s an excellent way to keep them out of Outwit range). The problem with these figures are that they can’t taxi anyone while soaring… so, if you’re using Sauron, you might be better off keeping him behind E Black Panther instead of just soaring him over to your opponent. Might be. Might be not (hmm… maybe I should’ve gone with Maybe instead of Might be… it would’ve been more fluid… something to keep in mind…). Also, cheap free moving fliers are awesome. For every reason that people like the grounded free movers as meillers, think of all of the fliers as phasers, and you have a new reason to use them. For more offensive pieces, I actually like phasing fliers to still operate as taxis (even Meteorite). They work well in the dual role. Every figure you plan on TKing, I’d keep hovering. It allows for more mobility in that area (key in these rules). Also, think about this: would it be more beneficial to keep your taxi in soaring and move it’s fare along the ground, so the two meet up at some point. Is it better for Torch to soar and then land at Invisible Girl’s level, or for Psylocke to move on her own and allow the Running Shot figures to meet up with her? Variety, man, that’s the way you’ve got to think. And keep in mind, figures with high move are much more able to work as taxis to bring figures back to the medics. Booster Gold kills the Support on a medic, stops next to a Batman who’s off Leap Climb, then takes him home so Ms. Checkmate can go to work on him. <br />
<br />
Has TK replaced taxing? In a way, yes. Do fliers still serve a major purpose that has yet to be fully discovered by the current meta of HeroClix game? A complete resounding echoing YES! Take some time, dust off the fliers that you haven’t used for a while (the ones who cost to much to be cheap taxis or had offensive capabilities weighing them down). Bring ‘em back to the board. You’ll be surprised at how much better they are and how much better you’ll play. I promise. <br />
<br />
Questions, Comments, Flames = D-Mail <br />
<br />
Adidas~ <br />
<br />
werdnA <br />
SonofVader <br />
